HOUSE RESOLUTION 14
By Hill
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Paul David Wood.
WHEREAS, the members of this legislative body were greatly saddened to learn of the
passing of Paul David Wood; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Wood was an exemplary gentleman who worked assiduously to
improve the quality of life for his fellow citizens in numerous capacities; and
WHEREAS, born in Sullivan County on September 8, 1954, to Doris Sandidge Wood
and Paul Junior Wood, Mr. Wood graduated from Lynn View High School in 1972 and began his
career at the Eastman Chemical Company, where he worked in fire maintenance until his well-
deserved retirement in 2006; and
WHEREAS, David Wood served the City of Church Hill for more than thirty-four years;
he became the city's second fire chief in 1986 and served as a building inspector until his full
retirement in 2019, after which time he spent his remaining years in the bosom of his family as a
loving husband, father, and grandfather; and
WHEREAS, a man of refined leisure, he was an avid outdoorsman who enjoyed hunting
and fishing with his grandsons; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Wood's industrious nature led him to learn carpentry and participate in
mission work, the latter of which was supremely expressive of his habitual care for those in
need; and
WHEREAS, a mentorial spirit, he was always willing to hand on what he had learned
through many years of practiced labor to the next generation, and his compassionate impact on
so many lives is incalculable; and
